    "31832509": {
      "title": "About the possibility to implement a nonuniform oversampling receive beamformer in a FPGA",
      "abstract": "A hardware implementation is presented in a context of receive beamforming based on nonuniform oversampling techniques. The digital beamformer with a nonuniform oversampling is made up of an analogue section containing the delta-sigma modulators and a digital section consisting of the following entities: Digital controller, FIFO buffers, Adder and Decimating Filter. The central entity of our design is the digital controller, which generate the non-uniform sampling clocks for driving the delta-sigma modulators and ensures the signals for FIFO buffers, adder and filter. The design has been simulated and implemented in an Altera FPGA. The device utilization shows that it is possible to implement in a single FPGA, containing memory blocks, every digital blocks of a beamformer."
    }
  },
